main event: A triangular or shaped object with a white light in front and two green lights behind was observed in Waterloo, Iowa on August 26, 1968.
interesting points: The object was observed for 3 minutes.
The observers were requested to complete a Form 117 but neither had returned it as of October 18, 1969.
The Aerial Phenomena Office requested the observers to complete the AF Form 117 and return it.
The Air Force indicated that the information received was not sufficient for a scientific investigation.
The possible causes listed include a private aircraft off course, a helicopter, or an illusion due to the observers being in a car.
sighted object: a triangular or shaped object with a white light in front and two green lights behind
